<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF711461FE184D21" blockId="6.[151,1436,1211,1358]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFF711461FE654D40" authority=": Dworakowska 1993" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,454,1303,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFF711461FF484D40" box="[151,235,1304,1327]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Igutettix</emphasis>
: Dworakowska 1993
</taxonomicName>
, Entomol. Abhandl. Staatl. Mus. Tierk. Dresden, 55: 99; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B50DB28D86CFBE1146EFB6E4D40" author="Hossain, M. S. &amp; Kwon, J. H. &amp; Suh, S. J. &amp; Kwon, Y. J." box="[1031,1229,1303,1327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="353 - 360" refId="ref6678" refString="Hossain, M. S., Kwon, J. H., Suh, S. J. &amp; Kwon, Y. J. (2021) A remarkable microleafhopper genus Koreoneura gen. nov. and newly recorded genus of the tribe Dikraneurini from Korea (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Zootaxa, 4951 (2), 353 - 360. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4951.2.8" type="journal article" year="2021">
Hossain 
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFBB91461FB284D40" box="[1119,1163,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
, Zootaxa, 4951: 357 (nec 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B50DB28D86CFF1F144FFE134D21" author="Matsumura, S." box="[249,432,1334,1358]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="93 - 120" refId="ref6800" refString="Matsumura, S. (1932) A revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental typhlocybid-genera with descriptions of new species and new genera. Insecta Matsumurana, 6 (3), 93 - 120." type="journal article" year="1932">Matsumura, 1932</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF711405FE534E6C" blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
Head with crown broadly rounded anteriorly. Pronotum large, more than 1.5 times as long as mesonotum. Fore wing with 2 
<superScript id="7C3C9BE9DB28D86CFF3814D9FF4D4DC1" attach="left" box="[222,238,1440,1454]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">nd</superScript>
apical cell stalked (or sometimes pointed) basally. Hind wing with vein RP fused to MP’ in apical ⅓; vein CuA branched more basally than point confluent with MP”. Male abdominal sternal apodemes short, exceeding anterior margin of 4 
<superScript id="7C3C9BE9DB28D86CFE911491FE274D99" attach="left" box="[375,388,1512,1526]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">th</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353652ADB28D86CFF211775FB254ED9" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF211775FB254ED9" blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFF211775FED84E49" bold="true" box="[199,379,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer roundly rectangular posteriad, bearing numerous setae scattered on surface, with or without dorsal process. Subgenital plate moderately long, about twice as long as valve, with concave outer margin, bearing macrosetae arranged in oblique row across plate and numerous fine setae on dorsal margin and apex. Style broad, with short apophysis and large preapical lobe. Connective T-shaped, with or without central lobe. Aedeagus tubular and slender, without process; shaft semicircular, curved dorsally; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353652ADB28D86CFF2117B9FCF34EB4" box="[199,848,1728,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF2117B9FCF34EB4" blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" box="[199,848,1728,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFF2117B9FEC24EB5" bold="true" box="[199,353,1728,1754]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palearctic region, Oriental region (
<collectingRegion id="498DF843DB28D86CFD0D17B9FCEF4EB4" box="[747,844,1728,1755]" country="China" name="Taiwan)" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Taiwan)</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353652ADB28D86CFF21179DFE744FB9" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF21179DFE744FB9" blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFF21179DFE984E91" bold="true" box="[199,315,1764,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFD0C179CFC704E90" authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1932" box="[746,979,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFD0C179CFCE44E91" box="[746,839,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Igutettix</emphasis>
Matsumura
</taxonomicName>
, because of the misidentification of the 
<typeStatus id="54F28803DB28D86CFF711670FF644F4C" box="[151,199,1801,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">type</typeStatus>
species of that genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B50DB28D86CFE071671FD464F4C" author="Dworakowska, I." box="[481,741,1800,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="97 - 139" refId="ref6637" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1993 b) Fusiplata Ahmed and some other Dikraneurini (Insects, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 55 (7), 97 - 139." type="journal article" year="1993">Dworakowska (1993b)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFC821671FC4B4F4D" authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[868,1000,1800,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFC821671FC4B4F4D" box="[868,1000,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished by the following features: fore wing 2 
<superScript id="7C3C9BE9DB28D86CFE991655FE2C4F55" attach="left" box="[383,399,1836,1850]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">nd</superScript>
apical cell stalked or pointed basally, hind wing vein CuA branched more basally, subgenital plates of male genitalia not fused to valve, style broad, and aedeagus simple. These features are common to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFAA31629FE744FE1" authority="Chiang, Hsu et Knight" authorityName="Chiang, Hsu et Knight" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraafrakra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFAA31629FF764FE1" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Paraafrakra</emphasis>
Chiang, Hsu et Knight
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F35E7631DB28D86CFDFC160DFDCC4FE1" box="[538,623,1908,1934]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and accordingly, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFCDE160DFC674FE1" box="[824,964,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraafrakra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFCDE160DFC674FE1" box="[824,964,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Paraafrakra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFAF4160DFA354FE1" authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[1298,1430,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFAF4160DFA354FE1" box="[1298,1430,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a result, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFEFB16E1FE024FDD" authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[285,417,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFEFB16E1FE024FDD" box="[285,417,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now comprises two species: 
